  "prompt": "What is actual meaning of life? Indeen, it depend on perception of people or other thing?",
  "response": "The meaning of life is a profound philosophical and existential question that has been debated by thinkers, philosophers, religious leaders, and individuals throughout human history. There's no single, universally accepted answer, but here are some perspectives:\n\n1. Subjective Perspectives:\n- Personal meaning varies for each individual\n- Can be shaped by:\n- Personal experiences\n- Cultural background\n- Individual beliefs\n- Personal goals and values\n\n2. Common Philosophical Perspectives:\n- Happiness and self-fulfillment\n- Contributing to society\n- Personal growth and learning\n- Creating meaningful relationships\n- Pursuing passion and purpose\n- Spiritual or religious understanding\n\n3. Different Cultural Views:\n- Western philosophy: Individual achievement\n- Eastern philosophy: Harmony and inner peace\n- Religious perspectives: Serving divine purpose\n- Existentialist view: Creating one's own meaning\n\n4. Scientific/Biological Perspective:\n- Survival and reproduction\n- Continuation of species\n- Adaptation and evolution\n\n5. Psychological Perspective:\n- Finding personal satisfaction\n- Developing meaningful connections\n- Self-actualization\n- Overcoming challenges\n\nUltimately, the meaning of life is deeply personal and can change throughout one's lifetime. There's no absolute, universal answer, but rather a continuous journey of understanding and creating meaning.",
